{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is the handoff between persistence and summary-save validation: the save path must read stored findings for the same round and reject PASS. A unit test of a pure predicate would miss wiring/query-scope bugs (e.g., wrong round filter, stale read, missing join). No real OS/network/LLM dependency is required.","test_description":"Create round R with persisted per-dimension findings including at least one FAIL. Attempt to persist a PASS summary for R through the real repository/service boundary. Assert the write is rejected (or transaction rolled back) with a validation error, and that a PASS summary row is not stored.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is specifically about data-source precedence across modules (gate evaluator vs summary text store). The real failure is wiring-level: gate trusting summary text instead of persisted findings. Unit tests of gate logic with injected inputs can miss incorrect repository calls or field mapping.","test_description":"Persist contradictory state for the same round: summary text says all PASS, but stored dimension findings include FAIL. Run stop-gate computation via the real evaluator + storage adapter. Assert final verdict is non-PASS (blocked/fail) based on stored findings, regardless of summary text content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Two module boundaries are essential: override authorization input and audit sink persistence. A unit test could verify flag parsing but still miss real failures where warning records are not emitted/stored or are detached from the override event.","test_description":"Attempt manual summary override without override flag and assert rejection. Repeat with override flag enabled through the real command/service path; assert override is accepted and an audit warning record is persisted with round/reviewer/timestamp/reason metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the review loop cannot finalize PASS unless a fresh review-agent round is executed on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"The failure emerges across the end-to-end review pipeline state machine: fix phase, diff update, review-round execution marker, then finalization gate. This is broader than a single module handoff and must validate sequence correctness across pipeline steps. Real LLM output quality is not required, but pipeline-step orchestration is.","test_description":"Run the pipeline through a round with FAIL findings, apply Phase 4 fixes that change diff, then try to finalize without running a new review-agent round. Assert PASS finalization is blocked with a reason indicating stale review round. Then execute a fresh review round on the updated diff and assert finalization can proceed (subject to findings).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.35,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.5}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings, the flow emits an escalation outcome instead of PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is policy enforcement over persisted round count + unresolved MUST-FIX findings + outcome emitter. The bug is typically in aggregation/state wiring, not OS/network/LLM behavior. A pure unit test can miss misread counters or unresolved-finding queries.","test_description":"Seed review history up to max rounds with at least one unresolved MUST-FIX finding. Invoke outcome computation via real orchestration/service modules. Assert emitted outcome is ESCALATION (or equivalent) and explicitly not PASS; verify escalation metadata includes unresolved finding references.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.04}}]}
